asense (0.2.2-1~ppa1~resolute1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Keep one NVML session for each live dGPU epoch instead of repeatedly
    initializing and shutting down NVML at the 1 Hz telemetry rate.
  * Prevent file-descriptor exhaustion on affected NVIDIA drivers while
    retaining passive runtime-power gating for a suspended hybrid dGPU.
  * Preserve the last verified controls when Refresh encounters a transient
    error, and keep the control completion worker alive across stale results.
  * Bound native resize correction state and the privileged mutation lock so
    neither can remain stuck indefinitely.
  * Decode USB-off charging as an enabled flag plus stored threshold, keeping
    the control available after disabling a previously selected 20% or 30%.
  * Fix the systemd sleep-hook argument order so post-resume reconciliation
    actually runs.
  * Require a full Debian package purge before switching to the standalone
    installer, preventing delayed package cleanup from affecting it.
  * Let standalone cleanup finish if its original desktop account was deleted,
    and ignore stale DKMS targets only after their kernel was removed.

 -- Fladirmacht <fladirmacht@gmail.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 05:15:00 +0200

asense (0.2.1-1~ppa1~resolute1) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Prevent standalone install/uninstall over a dpkg-managed installation.
  * Keep standalone-to-Debian migration and repeat package upgrades clean.
  * Write the selected desktop user through a real temporary file so package
    reinstall works with the Ubuntu 26.04 coreutils-from-uutils install tool.

 -- Fladirmacht <fladirmacht@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 23:05:00 +0200

